      "post_content": "@lorendorky   \n  \nThere's not exactly much in the ways of acceleration for white and blue. Red has some options, but you've got to be pretty lucky to draw into those cards at just the right time.  \n  \n@ZEvilMustache  \n  \nNo, but destroying two lands IS fun, however. Remember, White and Red are best known for the ways they can get double strike; [Assault Strobe](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Assault Strobe), [Concerted Effort](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Concerted Effort), [Double Cleave](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Double Cleave), [Rage Reflection](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rage Reflection), [Savage Beating](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Savage Beating), [True Conviction](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=True Conviction), [Psychotic Fury](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Psychotic Fury), [Sunhome, Fortress of the Legion](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sunhome, Fortress of the Legion). Those are basically all of the really useful ones that red and white have access to (there's a handful of others, but they do nothing but grant double strike). Combine that with white and blue's various ways of getting creature's through (via unblockability or protection from their creatures), as well as the equipment that gives trample, and Numot... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
